Busia Deputy Governor Kizito Wangalwa has urged Wiper boss Kalonzo Musyoka and Ford Kenya&rsquo;s Moses Wetang&rsquo;ula to support ODM&rsquo;s Raila Odinga for President.He said compared to his co-principals, the opposition leader is better placed to defeat President Uhuru Kenyatta next year. &ldquo;We will persuade our leaders Kalonzo and Wetang&rsquo;ula to willingly rally behind Odinga. We believe he will become the flagbearer,&rdquo; Wangalwa said.Addressing the press on Thursday in Kisumu town, he said the principals should unite if they want to form the next government.Wangalwa said the future of Kenya is in the hands of Cord, urging Kenyans to reject negative ethnicity and support Raila to bring about change.He acknowledged Kalonzo and Wetang&rsquo;ula are qualified for the country&rsquo;s top seat and have the ability to lead, but insisted Raila stands a better chance.In opinion polls, Raila has in most cases surpassed Wetang&rsquo;ula and Musyoka in popularity.&ldquo;Let us not focus on our selfish gains and instead give priority to the interests of Kenyans,&rdquo; Wangalwa said.The deputy governor said he is confident the opposition will trounce JP. He underscored the sacrifice Kenyans have made in the clamour for better leadership and democracy in the country, saying that should not be ignored. Wangalwa said the Cord coalition will rescue Kenyans from bad governance, massive corruption and oppression by the Jubilee administration. &ldquo;It is unfortunate Kenyans live in abject poverty yet there is a government in place in which a few individual enrich themselves through mega graft.&rdquo;